context: Revision rhinoplasty and left conchal cartilage harvest to correct nasal deformity.   (Medical Transcription Sample Report)

Revision rhinoplasty and left conchal cartilage harvest to correct nasal deformity.   (Medical Transcription Sample Report)

This patient is an otherwise healthy male who had a previous nasal fracture. During his healing, perioperatively he did sustain a hockey puck to the nose resulting in a saddle-nose deformity with septal hematoma.
During his healing, perioperatively he did sustain a hockey puck to the nose resulting in a saddle-nose deformity with septal hematoma.
he patient did have approximately 12 mL of Lidocaine with epinephrine 1% with 1:100,000 infiltrated into the nasal soft tissues.
Betadine was utilized for preparation
Hemostasis was obtained with bipolar electrocauterization.
Bovie electrocauterization was also employed as needed.
The patient then had a Telfa placed both anterior and posterior to the conchal defect
The patient then had a Telfa placed both anterior and posterior to the conchal defect and placed in a sandwich dressing utilizing a 2-0 Prolene suture.
Antibiotic ointment was applied generously
At this point, attention was turned to osteotomies and examination of the external cartilages.
Then, 5-0 Dexon was employed for intradomal suturing,
5-0 clear Prolene was used for interdomal suturing
A Gore-Tex small implant had been selected, previously incised.
Next, attention was turned to performing a columella strut.
The external columella inverted gull-wing incision along the nasal tip was closed with a series of interrupted everting 6-0 black nylon sutures
There was no evidence of hematoma, and the patient had a series of brown Steri-Strips and Aquaplast cast placed over the nasal dorsum.

. He was charged to home on antibiotics to prevent infection both from the left ear conchal cartilage harvest and also the Gore-Tex implant area
